div1.p: In the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the matter of the application of Ng Key Tung, for a writ of Habaeus Corpus.

Above named petitioner having made application to this Court for writ of habeaus by and through his father Get Tock addressed to the United States Commissioner of Immigration White, and to such persons or agents acting by, through or under them or in behalf of the U. S. Government, in whose custody the petitioner is shown by his petition to be confined and restrained of his liberty and to be ordered deported, as alleged in his petition illegally and unwarranted and without power, and not under virtue of or by authority of the Statutes of the United States, and the Court being fully advised, it is ordered thath the Honorable U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White, or such persons acting under or through said party and in behalf of the United States Government having custody of said petitioner NgKey Tung, show cause, if any they have before this Court at the Court room at the Federal Building in the City of Seattle on the 5th day of November Dec, 1914, at 10 o'clock in the aM. why said application should not be granted, and in the meantime U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White, as well as said persons who are acting under and through you, refrain and desist from deporting or placing, and removing said petitioner Ng. Key Tung from said Court District or carrying into effect any warrant or order for his deportation which may be held by you.

It is further ordered that said Ng Key Tung either by himself or through his attorney within deliver five days give over to the U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White, in charge of the Immigration Station at Seattle, Washington, such amount as he may demand as a fund for the keepxing of said Ng Key Tung until said action of this Court in hearing said petition or until such further action of the Government in relation to his case is concluded.
It is further ordered that a certified copy of this order shall be served upon the Honorable U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White.
United States of America, Western DISTRICT OF Washinton } ss:

I hereby certify and return that I served the anexed order to show cause on the therein-named Henry D White U S Immigration Commisioner
by handing to and leaving a true and correct copy thereof with him personally at Seattle Wash in said District on the 17th day of November, A. D. 1914
